                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/17/2003&nbsp;: 10:03:10 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> I dunno, IMO, there is a constant tradeoff between mana and hpts.  Both are equally important and you can't really say that mana &gt; hpts or mana &lt; hpts.  It all boils down on your playing style as to what you determine is important.  For me and my playing style, mana &gt; hpts because you're no good to anyone if you don't have mana to cast spells or if you are constantly OOM.  Yes I agree that having more hpts means that you can lich longer, but that also means more downtime because you have to med more often.<br /><br />I don't think I've ever had a hpt issue; even with the current hpts I have now.  With Shield of Maelin to buff my hpts a bit over 2k, I can usually make due with what I have.  Saryrn's Kiss usually heals me fine and I usually try to cast Saryrn's Kiss again on the mob just before it dies so I have an extra buffer; especially when I'm soloing and is expecting an extended downtime.  And if my hpts ever drop below 60%, I just click off SoS, even if I'm not FM, and cast it again when the fight starts.  ToM is also your friend.<br /><br />On raids or in groups, I rarely run out of mana or get low on hpts.  If I'm buffed with a druid's replenishment regen spell and have a bard playing their restoration songs, I can lich throughout the entire raid without a single hpt loss.  And if I'm in groups, there's usually enough mobs being pulled that I can heal myself with my taps so that my hpt loss from liching is at a minimum.<br /></span></font></td>
